    <class name="Limiter"
           c:symbol-prefix="limiter"
           c:type="DexLimiter"
           version="1.2"
           parent="Object"
           final="1"
           glib:type-name="DexLimiter"
           glib:get-type="dex_limiter_get_type"
           glib:fundamental="1">
      <doc xml:space="preserve"
           filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
           line="32">`DexLimiter` limits the number of operations running concurrently.

A limiter starts with a fixed number of permits. Use [method@Dex.Limiter.acquire]
and [method@Dex.Limiter.release] directly when a permit must cover a custom
scope, or use [method@Dex.Limiter.run] or
[method@Dex.Limiter.run_on_pool] to acquire a permit and release it
automatically when the work completes.</doc>
      <constructor name="new" c:identifier="dex_limiter_new" version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="476">Creates a new `DexLimiter` with @max_concurrency permits.

@max_concurrency must be greater than zero. Each successful acquisition
consumes one permit until [method@Dex.Limiter.release] is called.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="43"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="485">a new `DexLimiter`</doc>
          <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <parameter name="max_concurrency" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="478">the maximum number of concurrent operations</doc>
            <type name="guint" c:type="guint"/>
          </parameter>
        </parameters>
      </constructor>
      <method name="acquire" c:identifier="dex_limiter_acquire" version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="520">Acquires one permit from @limiter.

The returned future resolves to %TRUE when a permit has been acquired. Call
[method@Dex.Limiter.release] exactly once for each resolved acquisition.

If the returned future is discarded before the permit is acquired, the permit
is returned to the limiter when it becomes available. If @limiter is closed
before acquisition completes, the returned future rejects with
%DEX_ERROR_SEMAPHORE_CLOSED.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="49"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="534">a future that resolves when a permit is acquired</doc>
          <type name="Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="522">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="close" c:identifier="dex_limiter_close" version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="774">Closes @limiter.

Pending and future acquisitions reject with %DEX_ERROR_SEMAPHORE_CLOSED.
Permits already acquired remain valid, but releasing them after close will
not make them available for new work.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="72"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="none">
          <type name="none" c:type="void"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="776">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="close_after_drain"
              c:identifier="dex_limiter_close_after_drain"
              version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="589">Closes @limiter and waits for all queued and running work to complete.

After this function is called, new acquire attempts are rejected with
%DEX_ERROR_SEMAPHORE_CLOSED.

The returned future resolves to `%TRUE` once all outstanding pending acquire
futures and held permits are complete. Existing permit holders must still
eventually release.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="45"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="602">a [class@Dex.Future] that resolves to `true`</doc>
          <type name="Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="591">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="get_max_concurrency"
              c:identifier="dex_limiter_get_max_concurrency"
              version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="503">Gets the maximum number of permits available from @limiter.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="47"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="none">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="509">the maximum number of concurrent operations</doc>
          <type name="guint" c:type="guint"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="505">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="release" c:identifier="dex_limiter_release" version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="569">Releases one permit previously acquired from @limiter.

This must be called exactly once for each successful
[method@Dex.Limiter.acquire] unless the permit is managed by
[method@Dex.Limiter.run].</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="51"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="none">
          <type name="none" c:type="void"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="571">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="run" c:identifier="dex_limiter_run" version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="631">Runs @func while holding one permit from @limiter.

The returned future resolves or rejects with the result of the spawned fiber.
The permit is released automatically after the fiber resolves or rejects. If
the returned future is discarded after the fiber starts, the fiber is allowed
to complete so that the permit can be released.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="53"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="647">a future representing the spawned fiber</doc>
          <type name="Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="633">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
          <parameter name="scheduler"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     nullable="1"
                     allow-none="1">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="634">scheduler to spawn @func on, or %NULL for the thread default</doc>
            <type name="Scheduler" c:type="DexScheduler*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="stack_size" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="635">stack size for the spawned fiber, or zero to use the default</doc>
            <type name="gsize" c:type="gsize"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="func"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     scope="notified"
                     closure="3"
                     destroy="4">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="636">fiber function to run after a permit is acquired</doc>
            <type name="FiberFunc" c:type="DexFiberFunc"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="func_data"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     nullable="1"
                     allow-none="1">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="637">closure data for @func</doc>
            <type name="gpointer" c:type="gpointer"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="func_data_destroy"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     scope="async">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="638">destroy notify for @func_data</doc>
            <type name="GLib.DestroyNotify" c:type="GDestroyNotify"/>
          </parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="run_coroutine"
              c:identifier="dex_limiter_run_coroutine"
              version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="679">Runs @func while holding one permit from @limiter.

The returned future resolves or rejects with the result of the spawned
coroutine. The permit is released automatically after the coroutine resolves
or rejects. If the returned future is discarded after the coroutine starts,
the coroutine is allowed to complete so that the permit can be released.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="60"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="694">a future representing the spawned coroutine</doc>
          <type name="Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="681">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
          <parameter name="scheduler"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     nullable="1"
                     allow-none="1">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="682">scheduler to spawn @func on, or %NULL for the thread default</doc>
            <type name="Scheduler" c:type="DexScheduler*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="func"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     scope="notified"
                     closure="2"
                     destroy="3">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="683">coroutine function to run after a permit is acquired</doc>
            <type name="CoroutineFunc" c:type="DexCoroutineFunc"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="user_data"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     nullable="1"
                     allow-none="1">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="684">closure data for @func</doc>
            <type name="gpointer" c:type="gpointer"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="user_data_destroy"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     scope="async">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="685">destroy notify for @user_data</doc>
            <type name="GLib.DestroyNotify" c:type="GDestroyNotify"/>
          </parameter>
        </parameters>
      </method>
      <method name="run_on_pool"
              c:identifier="dex_limiter_run_on_pool"
              version="1.2">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
             line="724">Runs @thread_func on @pool while holding one permit from @limiter.

The returned future resolves or rejects with the result of the submitted
thread-pool work. The permit is released automatically after the work
resolves or rejects. If the returned future is discarded after the work is
submitted to @pool, the work is allowed to complete so that the permit can be
released.

Workers in `DexThreadPool` are not scheduler threads, so @thread_func must
not use `dex_await()`.</doc>
        <source-position filename="src/dex-limiter.h" line="66"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
               line="744">a future representing the submitted work</doc>
          <type name="Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <instance-parameter name="limiter" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="726">a `DexLimiter`</doc>
            <type name="Limiter" c:type="DexLimiter*"/>
          </instance-parameter>
          <parameter name="pool" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="727">a `DexThreadPool`</doc>
            <type name="ThreadPool" c:type="DexThreadPool*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="thread_func"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     scope="notified"
                     closure="2"
                     destroy="3">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="728">
  function to run on @pool after a permit is acquired</doc>
            <type name="ThreadFunc" c:type="DexThreadFunc"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="user_data"
                     transfer-ownership="none"
                     nullable="1"
                     allow-none="1">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="src/dex-limiter.c"
                 line="730">closure data for @thread_func</doc>
            <type name="gpointer" c:type="gpointer"/>
